<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1981</DATELINE><TITLE>Single radial haemolysis for the determination of antibody to reoviruses</TITLE><BODY>A single radial haemolysis (SRH) for reovirus antibody determination was developed and compared to standard haemagglutination-inhibition (HI) and complement fixation (CF) techniques. SRH appeared more simple and sensitive than CF, but less sensitive and less specific than HI.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>